_source.description: The purpose of this study is to collect and store tissue, blood, and sputum samples from patients with lung cancer to be tested in the laboratory. Collecting and storing samples of tissue, blood, and sputum from patients with cancer to study in the laboratory may help the study of cancer in the future.

groups.description: Peripheral blood, sputum, and biopsy specimens are collected from patients. Tissue samples are frozen and stored in a lung cancer specimen repository for later use in correlative studies.

outcome_measures.measure: Establishment of a central lung cancer specimen repository to serve as a resource for current and future scientific studies

_source.public_title: Collecting and Storing Samples From Patients With Lung Cancer
_source.scientific_description:
OBJECTIVES:  
I. Establish a central lung cancer specimen repository to serve as a resource for current and future scientific studies.
II. Correlate clinicopathologic information in the Southwest Oncology Group clinical data base with results of studies using the repository. 
III. Test new hypotheses with the specimens in the repository.

OUTLINE: 
Peripheral blood, sputum, and biopsy specimens are collected from patients. Tissue samples are frozen and stored in a lung cancer specimen repository for later use in correlative studies.
